Importing an existing Application in JenkinsX
 
Daemonset-
log collection on every node
storage collection on every node
monitoring agent on every node
Daemonset creates a pod on each node of the cluster
When a node is added a new pod is created
when the node is delete the pod is deleted
kubectl get pods -n kube-system
coredns
etc-master
kube-apiserver-master
kube-proxy
kube-controller-manager-master
kube-schduler-master
kubernetes-dashboard
tiller-deploy
calico-node
	

Daemonsets are running all the single nodes of the cluster

kubectl get ds -n kube-system
Name DESIRED CURRENT READY UP-TO-DATE AVAILABLE NODE SELECTOR AGE
kubectl edit ds -n kube-system calico-node
kubectl get ds -n rook-ceph
kubectl get ds --all-namespaces	
